You'll notice that the program will fail with message:

`System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException: 'Specified argument was out of the range of valid values. Parameter name: ModelFile'`

That is because the Resnet18 extension is looking for the model in the path created by [AssemblyPathHelper](https://github.com/dotnet/machinelearning/blob/master/src/Microsoft.ML.DnnImageFeaturizer.AlexNet/AssemblyPathHelpers.cs)

The path created points to the  **lib\netstandard2.0\DnnImageModels\**
the packages actually get downloaded in the  **\tools\DnnImageModels**  folder. 

Full path of the folders, inside the downloaded nuget packages. 
- constructed:  **microsoft.ml.dnnimagefeaturizer.resnet18\<version>\lib\netstandard2.0\DnnImageModels\**
- actual location of the DnnImageModels folder:  **microsoft.ml.dnnimagefeaturizer.resnet18\<version>\tools\DnnImageModels**

Need to construct the correct path.

Create a new console project, and try running the following sample:


